## Documentation is part of the deliverable
If a change affects setup, API contracts, DB schema, or user-facing flows, update documentation in the same change.

## Required docs (create when codebase appears)
- `README.md`
  - prerequisites (PHP, Composer, Node)
  - setup steps
  - environment variables list (names only, no secrets)
  - run commands (backend + frontend)
  - local URLs
- `API.md` or `docs/openapi.yaml`
  - auth method (Sanctum cookie vs token)
  - endpoint list with request/response examples
  - standard error shape
- `docs/auction-rules.md`
  - min increment rules
  - when auctions start/end
  - tie-breaking behavior (if two bids same time)
  - outbid notification behavior (real-time vs polling)

## Writing style
- Use clear, step-by-step instructions.
- Prefer copy-pastable commands.
- Keep docs consistent with the repo’s actual scripts and ports.
